Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.87,0:04:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:276873,279909}Who the hell are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.90,0:04:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:279909,283480}I don't think they're your\Nregular bandits looking for money.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.48,0:04:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:283480,286516}It looked like a provocation\Nagainst our government.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.35,0:04:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:287350,289219}A provocation?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.21,0:04:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:289219,293923}In other words, this whole Count Red\Nis a supporter of the Paris occupiers?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.72,0:04:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:294724,297060}In my opinion,\Nit is the only sensible option.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.76,0:05:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:297761,300096}Panza, and what do you\Nthink about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.49,0:05:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:300497,302932}I agree with this gentleman.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.14,0:05:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:316146,320583}In that case, they also obviously know\Nthat we want to sign a secret agreement
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.58,0:05:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:320583,324521}with the Prussian army and that\Nwe will try to sell Paris to them again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.78,0:05:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:324788,326923}This is a serious problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.92,0:05:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:326923,330393}If Count Red steals the document\Nthat Prussia is about to send to us
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.39,0:05:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:330393,335932}and make it public, we won't be\Nsafe anywhere in France.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.36,0:05:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:338368,343239}This document cannot see\Nthe daylight, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.23,0:05:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:343239,345441}I am fully aware of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.44,0:05:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:345441,347410}Panza, look out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.94,0:05:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:351948,353983}Count Red's minions!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.98,0:05:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:353983,355418}Panza, don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.41,0:05:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:355418,356452}But why, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.58,0:06:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:357587,360757}Now he will go to inform his leaders\Nabout our agreement with Prussia.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.25,0:06:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:362258,366563}You're so thick at times.\NHe's our pawn now!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.56,0:06:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:366563,367430}Our pawn?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.99,0:06:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:367997,373169}We'll smoke them out. The document\Nis just a bait that will let us find them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.16,0:06:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:373169,376072}You will receive\Nthe real document, Panza.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.07,0:06:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:376072,379175}We cannot afford another failure\Nlike the one in London, you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.17,0:06:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:379175,382946}Yes sir! I swear on my life\Nthat I will not let you down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.94,0:06:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:382946,384414}By the way, Mr. Thiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.41,0:06:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:384414,388952}How did it happen that we let Isabelle return\Nto Versailles, as if nothing had happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.81,0:06:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:389819,392255}It's Captain Langlois' wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.75,0:06:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:392755,394324}Captain Langlois'?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.65,0:06:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:394657,397994}He's popular with his subordinates\Nand easy to manipulate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.99,0:06:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:397994,402065}It's good to have some ace\Nup your sleeve.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.36,0:06:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:403366,406135}We'll use him\Nuntil he's worn out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.81,0:07:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:418815,421618}Isabelle, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.61,0:07:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:421618,427657}{\fscx95}Do you have any idea how much your ridiculous\Nbehavior hurt the Rostains' reputation?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.39,0:07:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:428391,434297}Father, I went to London\Nnot for our family, let alone for Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.29,0:07:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:434297,437567}I did it just to help my sister—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.56,0:07:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:437567,441271}Silence, Isabelle!\NI will not let you talk back to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.30,0:07:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:444307,448845}Ah, it's you, Victor. Do you think\Nthat I raised my children badly?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.84,0:07:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:448845,453616}Why is it that my children don't care at all\Nabout what is happening at home?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.25,0:07:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:454250,460290}I do not know. I abandoned money\Nfor a military career myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.29,0:07:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:460290,462659}I'm not the one that can\Nanswer your question.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.65,0:07:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:462659,467030}Victor. The Rostains are a venerable family\Nthat dates back three hundred years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.63,0:07:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:467630,471367}I could not bear the thought\Nthat our lineage would be forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.36,0:07:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:471367,473670}I just want to\Nprotect our heritage.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.67,0:07:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:473670,474404}Darling.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.13,0:08:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:476139,480610}Both Isabelle and Geneviève are proud\Nwomen, perfectly worth our family's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.61,0:08:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:480610,483880}Their actions are simply caused\Nby the times we live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.95,0:08:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:490954,493556}The times we live in…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.12,0:08:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:494123,495425}Mr. Victor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.79,0:08:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:495792,498728}A messenger from\NMr. Thiers came to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.22,0:08:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:499228,500863}What? From Thiers?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.96,0:08:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:502966,507437}Captain Langlois, you are ordered\Nto appear at the palace immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.74,0:08:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:518748,520183}Count Red?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.18,0:08:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:520183,525154}Yes. You are the only one\Nable to capture this criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.15,0:08:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:525154,529025}As far as I know, their group\Nis just a bunch of bandits.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.02,0:08:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:529025,532528}Shouldn't the police handle this?\NTo involve the army…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.52,0:08:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:532528,534864}Count Red is an enemy\Nof our country.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.86,0:08:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:534864,538167}Are you going to argue\Nwith my orders?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.76,0:09:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:538768,540436}No, not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.90,0:09:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:540903,543272}Here is my order,\NCaptain Langlois.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.27,0:09:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:543272,546376}Destroy the shadow army\Nled by Count Red.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.37,0:09:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:546376,549178}Understood? I have already\Nmade some preparations.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.22,0:09:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:562225,565128}{\i1}Victor against Count Red.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.12,0:09:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:565128,567964}{\i1}And so, these two men,\Nwho saved Isabelle in London,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.96,0:09:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:567964,571334}{\i1}were put at the ends\Nof their swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.34,0:10:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:649345,651380}Where have you been, Irma?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.38,0:10:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:651380,653483}I know, I know, but…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.48,0:10:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:653483,656486}I keep telling you\Nnot to risk unnecessarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.48,0:11:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:656486,660156}I want to be useful to you.\NBesides, we're both in this together.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.15,0:11:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:660156,662191}Together?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.69,0:11:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:663693,669298}All these weapons and jewels are to be\Nused to defend Paris and its people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.79,0:11:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:669799,671634}That's why…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.63,0:11:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:671634,673302}That's hardly a justification.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.73,0:11:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:674737,677940}"You are a woman.\NThe role of a woman lies elsewhere."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.94,0:11:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:677940,679976}I don't want to\Nlisten to this rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.64,0:11:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:682645,684981}Better tell me\Nwhat you think about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.98,0:11:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:684981,687984}Soon Prussia will secretly send some\Nimportant document to Versailles.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.98,0:11:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:687984,689652}What are you talking about?\NAre you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.56,0:11:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:699562,702798}{\i1}Neither Count Red\Nnor anyone from his shadow army
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.79,0:11:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:702798,707336}{\i1}could even guess that it was\Nyet another of Thiers' traps.
Comment: 0,0:12:16.83,0:12:16.83,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:736832,736832}Part B
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.70,0:12:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:770700,771801}What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.97,0:12:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:773970,777039}Please remain calm.\NWe are not interested in your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.03,0:12:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:777039,779642}All we're asking you\Nis to hand over that parcel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.25,0:13:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:795258,796325}Bloody hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.46,0:13:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:800463,802331}Count Red.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.33,0:13:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:802331,804033}Resistance is futile.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.73,0:13:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:804734,806769}{\i1}Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.30,0:13:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:807303,809505}You fell into our ambush.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.50,0:13:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:809505,812375}I do not like this method,\Nbut that was the order I was given.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.37,0:13:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:812375,814710}If you do not resist,\Nwe will spare you life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.08,0:13:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:819081,821484}Did I say anything funny?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.48,0:13:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:825488,827023}Look what I got here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.96,0:13:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:834964,836332}Get down!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.03,0:14:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:842038,843339}– Irma!\N– Dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.17,0:14:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:849178,850546}After them. After them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.47,0:14:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:874470,877239}{\i1}Not good. Behind these trees\Nthere's the Rostains' estate.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.66,0:15:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:899662,903866}Be good and nobody will get hurt.\NBelieve it or not, but we don't like killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.17,0:15:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:911173,914076}{\i1}As I thought,\Nthey took them hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.41,0:15:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:921417,926055}{\i1}Who would've thought that of all places,\Nwe're going to fight here. Life is so ironic.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.18,0:15:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:927189,929325}{\i1}Father. Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.76,0:15:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:931761,934363}Apparently,\Ntheir daughter is upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.36,0:15:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:934363,936232}I'll go check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.46,0:15:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:937466,939468}Just don't hurt her, Irma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.16,0:15:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:940169,942304}That depends on\Nwhat she will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.64,0:16:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:980643,982111}Stay calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.04,0:16:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:984046,986715}Don't struggle and I won't\Ndo anything to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.71,0:16:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:986715,987583}Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.58,0:16:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:987583,989418}One of the\NCount Red's shadows.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.68,0:16:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:990686,993088}It's… Is that you, Isabelle?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.63,0:16:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1004633,1006035}Enough of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.57,0:16:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1009572,1011173}Words out of my mouth,\Nmy friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.37,0:16:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1013375,1015478}Isabelle, cover yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.80,0:17:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1040803,1042171}{\i1}This fighting style…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.17,0:17:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1046175,1048043}{\i1}You're good, Andréa.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.78,0:17:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1053782,1055718}{\i1}That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.15,0:17:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1062157,1064360}Count Red… You are…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.96,0:17:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1066962,1072134}How about you remove your mask?\NCount Red, or rather… Andréa.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.06,0:17:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1073068,1076739}You saw through me, Victor.\NI can't say I'm surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.73,0:18:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1076739,1080142}Your fighting style gave you away.\NI could never forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.14,0:18:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1080142,1082778}I'm glad you're alive, Andréa.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.87,0:18:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1083879,1085748}Victor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.64,0:18:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1086649,1088884}What… What just happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.32,0:18:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1093322,1095958}I'm sorry you had to worry\Nbecause of me, Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.79,0:18:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1096792,1099395}Andréa… Andréa!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.39,0:18:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1099395,1100162}Isabelle!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.10,0:18:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1108103,1114510}{\i1}Yes. Count Red was to die\Nin the Battle of Champigny.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.51,0:18:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1114510,1119848}{\fscx95\i1}It was Andréa whom Thiers was supposed to put\Nto death in a battle with no chance of winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.49,0:18:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1132494,1134897}{\i1}After the Battle of\NChampigny was over,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.89,0:18:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1134897,1138534}{\i1}Andréa started wandering\Naimlessly on the verge of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.53,0:19:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1138534,1142871}{\i1}He was saved by a group\Nof Gypsies who were passing by.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.78,0:19:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1155784,1159822}{\i1}Under the tender care of Irma,\None of the gypsy girls,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.82,0:19:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1159822,1164827}{\i1}Andréa pulled through and\Neventually jumped back on his feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.13,0:19:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1172134,1179208}{\i1}Irma taught Andréa many things: sadness\Nand the hardships associated with poverty,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.20,0:19:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1179208,1183212}{\i1}but also the simple joy of life\Nand how to appreciate each day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.71,0:19:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1186715,1195658}{\i1}It was a life that Andréa,\Nborn to a wealthy family, never knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.65,0:20:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1195658,1202231}{\i1}Andréa saw for the first time\Nwhat he really wanted to protect.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.54,0:20:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1218547,1227656}{\i1}Spending day after day with each other,\NIrma and Andréa got very close.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.66,0:20:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1231660,1233696}{\i1}Dear…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.99,0:20:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1234997,1236699}{\i1}Irma.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.28,0:21:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1260289,1262991}Good job, Irma!\NThe girl has a taste!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.86,0:21:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1270866,1273836}{\i1}I can't sit here\Ndoing nothing forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.60,0:21:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1275604,1278140}{\i1}Somebody help me…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.31,0:21:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1288317,1295057}{\i1}Andréa understood\Nwhat he should be fighting for.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.16,0:21:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1303165,1307603}All my brothers in arms\Nwho survived the Battle of Champigny
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.60,0:21:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1307603,1309972}pledged to take\Nrevenge on Thiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.97,0:21:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1309972,1315744}By taking revenge on him, we will\Nsave the oppressed citizens of Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.74,0:21:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1315744,1318447}Over time, more and more\Npeople joined us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.44,0:22:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1318447,1323418}Soon we formed an army of shadows\Nand I became Count Red.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.31,0:22:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1324319,1327623}You do realize, however,\Nthat you are breaking French law?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.62,0:22:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1328624,1333595}Laws made by villains from Versailles such as\NThiers don't amount to a spit in the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.59,0:22:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1333595,1336965}We respect the laws\Nof people who protect Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.96,0:22:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1336965,1340736}What would you say, Victor,\Nif I suggested you to join us?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.33,0:22:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1342337,1344907}I am a soldier of the\NVersailles government.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.90,0:22:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1344907,1348977}Whatever the government,\Nas a soldier, I must obey its orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.14,0:22:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1350145,1352848}You haven't changed at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.92,0:22:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1358921,1359855}What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.92,0:22:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1360923,1361990}What's going on there?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.99,0:22:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1361990,1364026}Trouble, boss! It's the army!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.02,0:22:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1364026,1367329}The French army surrounded\Nthe mansion and they're shooting at us!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.86,0:22:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1367863,1371266}The French troops? But why?\NWhy are they attacking the Rostains' estate?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.96,0:22:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1371967,1373902}What's going on in Thiers' head?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.10,0:22:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1374102,1377172}Victor, now you can see\Nwhat a rat he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.81,0:23:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1386815,1390719}The Rostain family\Ngives shelter to Count Red.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.71,0:23:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1390719,1393555}This is treason.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.55,0:23:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1393555,1397192}Their property is hereby confiscated\Nby the government of Versailles!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.39,0:23:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1398393,1403031}{\i1}Count Red. Inadvertently,\Nyou have done us a huge favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.03,0:23:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1403031,1406869}{\i1}Thanks to you,\Nthe Rostains' assets will be ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.21,0:23:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1418213,1421483}{\i1}Crumbling walls and pillars.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.08,0:23:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1422084,1427723}{\i1}Isabelle, seeing the sudden collapse\Nof the Rostain family, forgot everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.72,0:23:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1427723,1431460}{\i1}She just stood speechless and looked\Nat the hell raging around her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.79,0:23:56.83,Credits,[credits],0,0,0,,{TIME:1431793,1436832}{\fad(200,200)\c&HFAFAFA&\blur1\fs20\an5\pos(580,410)\t(2972,4972,5,\c&H101010&)}To be continued
Comment: 0,0:23:57.49,0:23:57.49,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:1437499,1437499}Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.49,0:24:00.46,Default,(sign),0,0,0,,{TIME:1437499,1440469}Next episode preview
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.07,0:24:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1442070,1445607}Thiers' attack sweeps away\Nmy family's mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.60,0:24:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1445607,1448277}Mom loses her life\Ncrushed by a chandelier.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.27,0:24:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1448277,1453148}Moments later, our father follows her.\NNothing makes any sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.14,0:24:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1453148,1460289}My brother, Victor and I barely escape.\NTogether with Jean, we decide to go to Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.28,0:24:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1460289,1462824}Next time on "Isabelle of Paris":
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.82,0:24:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1462824,1467462}"I Hate The War That Killed Mother".\NPlease look forward to it.
